{"id": "EUVD-2021-26770", "enisaUuid": "f42f57a3-ef60-3279-9efc-062f3def25c3", "description": "The bpf verifier in the Linux kernel did not properly handle mod32 destination register truncation when the source register was known to be 0. A local attacker with the ability to load bpf programs could use this gain out-of-bounds reads in kernel memory leading to information disclosure (kernel memory), and possibly out-of-bounds writes that could potentially lead to code execution. This issue was addressed in the upstream kernel in commit 9b00f1b78809 (\"bpf: Fix truncation handling for mod32 dst reg wrt zero\") and in Linux stable kernels 5.11.2, 5.10.19, and 5.4.101.", "datePublished": "2021-03-23T17:45:13", "dateUpdated": "2024-09-16T17:27:58", "baseScore": 7.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:H/PR:L/UI:N/S:C/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://www.suse.com/security/cve/CVE-2021-3444.html", "https://ubuntu.com/security/CVE-2021-3444", "https://linux.oracle.com/cve/CVE-2021-3444.html", "https://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/torvalds/linux.git/commit/?id=9b00f1b78809", "https://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2021/03/23/2", "http://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2021/03/23/2", "http://packetstormsecurity.com/files/162117/Kernel-Live-Patch-Security-Notice-LSN-0075-1.html", "https://security.netapp.com/advisory/ntap-20210416-0006/", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2021/10/msg00010.html", "http://packetstormsecurity.com/files/164950/Kernel-Live-Patch-Security-Notice-LSN-0082-1.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2021-3444"], "assigner": "canonical", "epss": 0.09, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "62172965-b935-3443-ada2-89de04cd7d40", "product": {"name": "Kernel"}, "product_version": "trunk <5.12-rc1"}, {"id": "709e88ec-05e9-3c7e-99c5-a14353f41696", "product": {"name": "Kernel"}, "product_version": "5.4 <5.4.101"}, {"id": "9eeb2554-36d7-3ae0-9f1a-a76cf2098182", "product": {"name": "Kernel"}, "product_version": "5.11 <5.11.2"